# views/puzzles.go — EARLY (puzzles)

Minimal Go handler for the Puzzles surface. Serves five
endpoints:

- `/gopher/puzzles/` — HTML page (nav chrome + a root div +
  puzzles.js bootstrap script).
- `/gopher/puzzles/puzzles.js` — compiled Elm bundle read
  from `games/lynrummy/elm/puzzles.js`.
- `/gopher/puzzles/catalog` — Python-generated puzzle
  catalog JSON, paired with a freshly-allocated session_id.
- `/gopher/puzzles/actions` — POST one wire action; appends
  to `lynrummy_elm_puzzle_actions`.
- `/gopher/puzzles/annotate` — POST one reader annotation;
  appends to `lynrummy_puzzle_annotations`.

All puzzle-session creation and action persistence happens
through the dedicated puzzles endpoints (catalog, actions),
not the full-game `/gopher/lynrummy-elm/` endpoints — the
puzzle actions table carries `puzzle_name` in every row
without nullables.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY (puzzles). Active and stable. New
  puzzles-only persistent state (catalog mining inputs,
  named annotation streams) lands here.

## Registered at

`views/registry.go`:

```go
mux.HandleFunc("/gopher/puzzles/", HandlePuzzles)
mux.HandleFunc("/gopher/puzzles", HandlePuzzles)
```

## Build-step

`ops/start` compiles `Puzzles.elm` to `puzzles.js`
alongside the main client's build. Rebuild is non-fatal —
on failure the handler returns a 404 pointing at the
explicit `elm make src/Puzzles.elm --output=puzzles.js`
recipe.

## Pointers

- Elm app: `games/lynrummy/elm/src/Puzzles.elm`.
- Main app handler (reused for full-game play +
  persistence): `views/lynrummy_elm.go`.
